# üêû bug report
Relative urls are not working as expected for empty paths when navigate between parent-child routes in the lazy loaded modules

### Affected Package
The issue is caused by package @angular/router

### Description

- Navigate to child-component (./child1-component)
- Navigate back to parent (../)
- Navigate to child-component again (./child1-component). 
- But it tries to navigate to "//child1-component" & throws an error

```
Routes in app module (forRoot)
const routes: Routes = [
  { 
    path: '',
    loadChildren: 'app/lazy/lazy.module#LazyModule' 
  },
];
```

```
Lazy loaded module routes (forChild)
const routes: Routes = [
  {
    path: '',
    component: LazyComponent,
    children: [
      {
        path: 'child1-component',
        component: BComponent
      },
      {
        path: 'child2-component',
        component: CComponent
      },
    ]
  }
];
```


## üî¨ Minimal Reproduction
https://stackblitz.com/edit/relative-link-lazy-loading

## üî• Exception or Error
Error: Uncaught (in promise): SecurityError: Failed to execute 'pushState' on 'History': A history state object with URL 'https://%28child1-component%29/' cannot be created in a document with origin 'https://relative-link-lazy-loading.stackblitz.io' and URL 'https://relative-link-lazy-loading.stackblitz.io/'.


